  "rationale": "This supervisor prioritizes forward motion in clear corridors, uses commit states to enforce consistent rotation or forward motion, and employs recovery/escape states after obstacle detection. Each state responds to all uncontrollable events, and only one primary controllable action is enabled per state (except obs_front, which allows both move_backward and full_rotate for escape). Commit states ensure that once a rotation or forward move is started, it continues until path_clear is detected, then transitions to forward_commit. Helper states prevent immediate re-entry to forward after obstacle detection, reducing oscillation and improving coverage.",
